<br>
After the Incident, it was learned that Trompen wasn't completely ready for Ragefire, as he would have been in his Original Form.  ie: Trompen didn't have the King's Note, nor the Pearl from Sol B.  <br>
<br>
I know that out-of-sequence camping is doable with the New Ragefire, but I thought that the &quot;Gentlemen's Agreement&quot; had taken this into consideration, and the Honor System was in place? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uroggulbuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roggulbuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede Slavedriver</span><br>  Posts: 476<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/24/02 4:05:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ragefire Agreement question</span><hr size=1> Tough call. <br>
<br>
Personally, I think a cleric camping ragefire before they have all the other pieces is a bit greedy: In that week or two that you are holding the camp, another cleric could have actually *gotten* their epic. <br>
<br>
The Ragefire is a bottleneck for so many clerics who *are* ready for the piece, to compound the problem with clerics camping it before they are ready? Doens't seem like good sense to me. <br>
<br>
Hell, hardest part right? Why not get it out of the way first, right? Yeah, and while you've got Begurgle's crown sitting in the bank next to the unpure heart of ragefire, and you're off on your rogue alt... <br>
<br>
Extreme example, but personally, I'd like to see clerics agree to leave RF alone until they actually can turn in that one part and get the epic. <br>
<br>
So, as an official standpoint, Clan Bashemded will not attempt to camp ragefire for a cleric that does not have the remainder of the quest finished in full. <br>
<br>
I would think it's not much to ask, seeing as how the camp is so ungodly anyway, that others do the same. But that's me. <br>
<br>
Whenever I play a cleric to 50+, I'll come back and be a little more direct about my ideas of the camp. *wink*<br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
