Lukieb <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uroggulbuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roggulbuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede Slavedriver</span><br>  Posts: 481<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/27/02 11:56:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ragefire Agreement question</span><hr size=1> The wait is long. <br>
<br>
It will be made longer if clerics who are not on their last step camp it. <br>
<br>
If it doesn't matter what step the cleric is on, the cleric could start their epic with the Ragefire camp, by that logic. <br>
<br>
Would you say that a level 49 cleric camping it is &quot;get[ting] it over with while they can.&quot;? If you think that a level 49 cleric should be camping ragefire, what about a level 48? 47? when does the number become too low? 46? 36? <br>
<br>
Yes, the game mechanics have changed in that you can now get the ragefire piece out of the old order. What *I* am saying, though, is that we should maintain the old mechanics through our actions: that is, just because you are now *able* to camp ragefire without the king note, doesn't mean that you *should*.<br>
<br>
If all that matters is when it is convienient for the cleric, then they could start the camp whenever they wanted. That's fine, if there was only one cleric on the server that needed the epic. <br>
<br>
However, being that there is more than just one cleric that needs their epic, the best way to try to reduce the length of the line to camp it, is to make sure that people only camp it when they are ready for it. It just stands to reason that the number of clerics that want their epic is greater than the number of clerics who are on the last step of their epic. <br>
<br>
The list, by the way, was a really bad idea that started off with the best intentions. The six month long waiting list was a *much* bigger bottleneck than our 4 week line up. <br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway, if the situation is not as obvious to you as it is to me, I'm sure it will get itself figured out fairly fast. <br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
