<br>
I would offer that all guilds capable of killing the King are able to kill ragefire, but that the reverse is not true. Ragefire is a (usually) solo mob, in an outdoor zone. The king is placed in a zone where, upon a total party wipe out past a locked door, you're coffin shopping. <br>
<br>
In any event, the point about where a cleric is in their epic is moot: We cannot verify where a cleric is in the quest, and on top of that, if the cleric is willing to camp ragefire before being &quot;ready&quot; for ragefire, not having every piece is still not an excuse to take it from them. Sure, life would be better if they'd wait on it, but sometimes life is not always that way.<br>
<br>
So, right, we've gotten past that &quot;cleric must be on the last step&quot; hurdle that we've been having. Best case: clerics understand that making the camp harder for everyone also makes it harder for them. Reality: Some people are stupid about things like that, and would rather have a heart in their bank than an epic on another cleric. To each their own, or whatever we have to say to agree to disagree on this point. <br>
<br>
However: Given the resources we have to work with, this camp *cannot* be moved to FFA, or any other variation on a race. Why not?<br>
<br>
Because guilds that can kill the king do not usually, have the resources available to them to race and beat guilds like SoT, BotS, NB, Tindi, etc to a mob in an outdoor zone with port locations for wizards and druids. <br>
<br>
Making Ragefire a FFA mob will create a situation in which cleric epics will go to the largest guilds first, and only when those largest guilds no longer have clerics who need their epics, only then will other clerics begin to have access to the mob. However, lets not forget that the larger guilds, in a FFA situation, do not have anything stopping them from killing ragefire for alts, friends, alts of friends, etc etc. For every member of a large guild that has a cleric alt, there's *another* ragefire that would go to one of the big guilds on the server, before a small guild would see even one. Not a good system. <br>
<br>
Sorry, but if you cannot see why that is unfair, I don't think that you should be allowed to play with other people and/or sharp objects. <br>
<br>
(the 'you' in that statement is not a directed one, it's meant to frame the discussion only, not to point at an individual.)<br>
<br>
A rotation/waiting list is a horribly bad idea. I promise, no matter how much people bring it up, no matter how tired I get of explaining why it is a bad idea, I will always point out why it is a bad idea. <br>
<br>
It creates a situation in which people have to wait for months, not weeks for ragefire. A five month wait, is longer than a 4 to 5 week long wait, especially when the &quot;list&quot; is not enforcable by any means at all. If the cleric is not *in the zone* and *online* than the list becomes totally useless, as opportunists rightfully take advantage of the opportunity. <br>
<br>
If, in the same breath, you say that &quot;If a cleric is willing to camp for 4 or 5 weeks, it doesn't matter what step of their epic they are on&quot;, it is counter productive to then say &quot;but I think a list is better because then the cleric doesn't have to camp for any time, they just wait until their turn on the list is up&quot;. <br>
<br>
First: Their turn on the &quot;list&quot; means what? That they show up after ragefire pops, and then get the spawn? <br>
<br>
Should a guild that is not on the list, be expected to pass up Zordak Ragefire spawned in Skyfire, when they are the only ones in the zone, because the cleric on the list may log on later in the day? That is *not* what would happen. I'm sorry, but even as I understand it with the larger rotation mobs, if you are not able to kill it within a reasonable time, the mob moves to the next group on the rotation. If the group in question does not even have their cleric online, how can they have a legitimate claim? They can't, and Rage becomes a FFA. <br>
<br>
Second: Getting on this list. How many guilds are able to kill ragefire? I would say, given enough warning, as a protected, totally reserved spawn would provide, that at least all the guilds able to go to the planes, per the RTA rules, would be able to kill ragefire. There are 24 planable entities on the links page alone, to say nothing of those who do not have links off that page. <br>
<br>
So, assuming 20 guilds, for both ease of calculation and oversimplifying the number involved to prove my point more convincingly if one realizes the number would be quite higher in practice than in theory...<br>
<br>
Our previous convention was that a guild could have one cleric on the list at a time. That would make a 20 week waiting period for a guild to get put on the list for a second sprinkler. It would also mean that the last person on this 'list' would have a 20 week waiting period to get the first sprinkler. <br>
<br>
Five months. Five months, with a good chance of losing the spawn if you are offline, or unable to get to a spawn fast enough, is a hell of a sight worse than a one month wait, with a gaurenteed shot at the spawn when it comes up for you. <br>
<br>
The reason that the list is now 4 or 5 clerics deep is *not* because it is in skyfire, not sol b. It is because the spawn timer is almost doubled from the old one. If the spawn had been a 72 hour one, from the moment they moved it out of Sol B, there would be *double* the amount of ragefires since it happened. And no, that would not mean the list would be 2 or 3 clerics long instead of 4 or 5. It means that there would be no line, or at most, 1 cleric extra, because there would be a least, what, 10 more hearts that would have dropped in the same amount of time? <br>
<br>
Why hasn't verant fixed that? Because they are trying to limit the number of cleric epics on a server. They can program a spawn time to whatever they want to. 8 hour spawns, 2 hour spawned placeholders with a 24 hour spawn after the place holder dies before the rare pops, 24 hour spawns plus or minus 8 hours, they can program any spawn they'd like. And ragefire is now a 5 to 7 day timer, because they are asses about it. <br>
<br>
In any event, a list, as has been said *many* times before, is a nice thought, but is a *stupid* plan in practice. It will cause many disagreements, many hard feelings. <br>
<br>
Free For All will mean &quot;epics for some&quot;, not 'all' as is implied in the title of 'free for all'. It is a nice theory, to race to the mob, but in the case of Ragefire, a race is not only unfair, it's cruel, as a cleric sees two of their guild members online at 8 am, while another guild comes in and kills ragefire. <br>
<br>
What does that promote? <br>
<br>
Clerics who want their epic, can't be in a guild that can't kill a level 60 mob on zero notice in under 60 seconds, from port in to dead. <br>
<br>
Kudos to those of you who can. Try not to forget those who can't.<br>
<br>
Ragefire should be, and hopefully will always remain a &quot;sit there and wait&quot; camp. Until Verant makes the spawn timer 3 days, as it was before, and/or makes it a triggered spawn like faydedar, then the best solution that the rathe has, without decending into the stupid and debasing culture of the FFA ragefire, is to continue the camp as it is. <br>
